Quote:  Ferns and tree-ferns flourish [on Stewart Island], ... supple-jack entwines your heels, and stinkwood is garlanded with little red flowers. There is red or black beech, there is mutton-bird scrub with thick green leaves that have white undersides, there are, perhaps, a dozen others.
